docs.abstract: The platinum-selling country trio will be known as the Chicks, the latest example of sweeping cultural changes brought on by nationwide protests spotlighting racial inequality.
docs.snippet: The platinum-selling country trio will be known as the Chicks, the latest example of sweeping cultural changes brought on by nationwide protests spotlighting racial inequality.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Dixie Chicks are now the Chicks.

headline.main: The Dixie Chicks Change Their Name, Dropping the ‘Dixie’
headline.print_headline: The Dixie Chicks Rebrand, Stealthily Ditching ‘Dixie’

docs.abstract: The Defense Department’s top intelligence official said that he had not been ordered to conduct surveillance on citizens, and that he supported their right to demonstrate peacefully.
docs.snippet: The Defense Department’s top intelligence official said that he had not been ordered to conduct surveillance on citizens, and that he supported their right to demonstrate peacefully.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A top Pentagon official has told Congress that the nation’s military intelligence agencies did not spy on American protesters during the wave of nationwide demonstrations against the police killings of African-Americans.

headline.main: Pentagon Denies Spying on Americans Protesting Police Killings
headline.print_headline: Pentagon Says It Has Not Spied on American Protesters

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, tried to get ahead of a week of intense scrutiny for him and his company by visiting several top lawmakers in Washington on Monday and reiterating how sorry he was for the social network’s failings.

docs.abstract: Donald J. Trump’s presidency meant snarled traffic, blocked sidewalks and frequent protests outside his Manhattan home.
docs.snippet: Donald J. Trump’s presidency meant snarled traffic, blocked sidewalks and frequent protests outside his Manhattan home.
docs.lead_paragraph: Traffic choked by cement barricades. Sidewalks blocked by police checkpoints. Protest after protest clogging the streets. For more than four years, life in the shadow of Donald J. Trump’s namesake tower on Fifth Avenue has been one intractable snarl.

headline.main: Trump Tower’s Neighbors Are Relieved as Barricades Come Down
headline.print_headline: Trump Tower’s Barricades Come Down, and Neighborhood Exhales

docs.abstract: Mr. Floyd was arrested in Houston over a $10 drug transaction. Now thousands of cases involving the officer who arrested him and his squad are under review.
docs.snippet: Mr. Floyd was arrested in Houston over a $10 drug transaction. Now thousands of cases involving the officer who arrested him and his squad are under review.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — In many of Houston’s struggling neighborhoods, a black undercover narcotics officer worked for decades, making bust after bust.

headline.main: Probe of Old Drug Cases Raises Questions About 2004 George Floyd Arrest
headline.print_headline: 2004 Arrest of Floyd  Receives New Scrutiny In Inquiry Into Officer

docs.abstract: The National Domestic Workers Alliance is putting nannies, housekeepers and home care workers at the center of the labor and progressive political movement.
docs.snippet: The National Domestic Workers Alliance is putting nannies, housekeepers and home care workers at the center of the labor and progressive political movement.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The three women knocking on doors around Las Vegas on Tuesday afternoon wanted to talk to people about the importance of voting, especially in a state with low voter turnout. They gave all the logistical details — where to go, what time to get there — and explained how early voting worked.

headline.main: To This Group, Labor Is More Than a ‘White Man Who Works in a Factory’
headline.print_headline: Building a Potent Alliance Of Nannies and Caregivers

docs.abstract: Special screenings and performances of black films and plays tailored for black audiences can feel especially welcoming.
docs.snippet: Special screenings and performances of black films and plays tailored for black audiences can feel especially welcoming.
docs.lead_paragraph: A handful of playwrights, directors, filmmakers and film lovers have created spaces for black audiences to crack jokes and clap back without apology and, afterward, process complex, nuanced race-related issues.

headline.main: At ‘Black Out’ Performances, the Power of Healing Through Community
headline.print_headline: The Healing Power of a Black Audience

docs.abstract: As a range of players called for unity and understanding in response to the killing of George Floyd in Minneapolis, the debate over Colin Kaepernick and his campaign for social justice resurfaced.
docs.snippet: As a range of players called for unity and understanding in response to the killing of George Floyd in Minneapolis, the debate over Colin Kaepernick and his campaign for social justice resurfaced.
docs.lead_paragraph: The outbreak of civil unrest initiated by the death of George Floyd has brought about an unusual outpouring from players, coaches and officials in the N.F.L., which has wrestled publicly with issues of race and racism more than other leagues. In some instances, however, longstanding disputes about whether the league takes the issue seriously enough have been rekindled.

headline.main: Athletes’ Outpouring on Civil Unrest Rekindles Kaepernick Debate in N.F.L.
headline.print_headline: Kaepernick Has More Allies in N.F.L., Years Later

docs.abstract: Robert Fuller’s sister said on Saturday that the initial determination by officials that her brother died by suicide did not make sense.
docs.snippet: Robert Fuller’s sister said on Saturday that the initial determination by officials that her brother died by suicide did not make sense.
docs.lead_paragraph: City officials in Palmdale, Calif., said on Saturday that they support calls by activists and residents who have demanded an independent investigation into the death of a 24-year-old black man who was found hanging from a tree in a public square this week.

headline.main: A Black Man Was Found Hanging From a Tree, and a Community Demands Answers
